title: JazzWerk Nonett
description:
JazzWerk Nonett live at Birdland Hamburg. A nine-piece ensemble featuring trumpet, flugelhorn, saxophones, flute, trombone, euphonium, piano, bass, and drums.
Roster: Steve Wiseman (trumpet, flugelhorn) @stevewisemantrumpet, Claas Ueberschär (trumpet, flugelhorn), Tadeus (alto saxophone, soprano saxophone, flute) @tadeus1959, Ralph Reichert (tenor saxophone, flute), Erik Konertz (trombone, bass trombone, euphonium) @konertzerik, Barry King (baritone saxophone, bass clarinet, flute) @barry.king69, Dirk Bleese (piano) @dirkbleese, Felix Behrendt (bass), Dirk Achim Dhonau (drums) @dirkachimdhonau.

_search_en.description: Critical Music presents an evening of intelligent, danceable Drum'n'Bass at the pulse of the underground. Kasra delivers technically precise, bass-focused sets. Mefjus is known for his detailed, energetic sound between tech aesthetics and emotional drive. Sequent adds deep liquid sounds and technoid facets. Support from Survey, N'Dee, MC Jamie White. Box 2 hosted by the Bassism Crew with Vilify, Eklekt1k, Grzly Adams, and Tommy Lexxus.

title: Clara Haberkamp »Classical & Jazz in Dialogue«
description: Pianist Clara Haberkamp explores the intersection of classical and jazz. She performs with her Trio (Oliver Potratz, Jarle Vespestad) and in Duo Azadi with cellist Atena Eshtiaghi. Two diverse concert halves where classical and jazz engage in dialogue.
